data.name: EnhancedCustomShapePath
desc: This service may be represented by a com.sun.star.beans.PropertyValue [].

types.name: Coordinates
desc: This property is specifying the points that makes the geometry of the shape.

types.name: GluePointLeavingDirections
desc: This property specifies GluePoint leaving directions.

types.name: GluePoints
desc: This property specifies custom glue points.

types.name: Segments
desc: This property specifies the commands and the way the Coordinates have to be interpreted.

types.name: SubViewSize
desc: This property specifies view size per sub path.

types.name: TextFrames
desc: This property specifies the text frames that can be used with the shape.
In general the first text frame is used, except the shape is containing vertical text, then the object tries to use the second text frame. The default text frame will be as big as the shape.

properties.name: ConcentricGradientFillAllowed
desc: This property specifies if this shape supports concentric gradient fill.
The default is false.

properties.name: ExtrusionAllowed
desc: This property specifies if this shape supports the EnhancedCustomShapeExtrusion properties.
The default is true.

properties.name: GluePointType
desc: This property defines the GluePoint type.
The values that can be used are specified in com.sun.star.drawing.EnhancedCustomShapeGluePointType

properties.name: StretchX
desc: This property specifies the horizontal StretchPoint that has to be used.
No stretching is used if this property is omitted.

properties.name: StretchY
desc: This property specifies the vertical StretchPoint that has to be used.
No stretching is used if this property is omitted.

properties.name: TextPathAllowed
desc: This property specifies if this shape supports concentric gradient fill.
The default is false;
